<TITLE> Recession won't affect Bangladeshis in Saudi Arabia: Muhith </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 28 (bdnews24.com)The finance minister said on Thursday that the ongoing global financial crunch would not affect the Bangladeshi workers employed in Saudi Arabia. AMA Muhith told reporters after a meeting with Saudi ambassador Abdullah Bin Nasser Al Bushairy that the envoy had has assured him that Bangladeshi workers will not be affected due to the current global economic meltdown. "The Bangladeshis there are in great shape and they're working very well," he quoted Al Bushairy as aying. "After assumption of office as finance minister, this was my first meeting with the Saudi Arabian ambassador," said Muhith. Muhith said Saudi Arabia is Bangladesh's largest labour market since about half of the expatriate workers are in that country alone. There are about 2.2 million Bangladeshi workers in Saudi Arabia now. bd
